A very very crude port of postmarkup, from http://code.google.com/p/postmarkup/wiki/Usage to Python3

I made it work at all ;)


Threepwood:postmarkup-1.1.4 e1ven$ python3
Python 3.2.1 (default, Dec  7 2011, 12:17:14) 
[GCC 4.2.1 (Based on Apple Inc. build 5658) (LLVM build 2335.15.00)] on darwin
Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more information.
>>> import postmarkup
>>> xhtml = postmarkup.render_bbcode("[b]For the lazy, use the render_bbcode function.[/b]")
>>> print(xhtml)
<strong>For the lazy, use the render_bbcode function.</strong>
>>> exit()

